title: Emily Ratajkowski focuses on fashion duty in Milan
text:
Emily Ratajkowski spent her Tuesday evening at a Milan location of TWINSET Simona Barbieri, for which she's starred in a campaign.
The 25-year-old flung a stylish white coat over a faintly sheer white top that was tight enough to showcase her impressively trim midriff.
Her hair wound into an updo, she'd slipped on a pair of high-waisted, loose white slacks and gleaming stilettos.
Scroll down for video
A night in Italy: Emily Ratajkowski spent her Tuesday evening at a Milan location of TWINSET Simona Barbieri, for which she's starred in a campaign
Ratajkowski, who rocketed to fame prancing about in the controversial music video for Robin Thicke's 2013 single Blurred Lines, toted a snakeskin-patterned purse.
She's joined Sasha Pivovarova in a rock-infused ad , released last month, for TWINSET Simona Barbieri's Spring/Summer 2017 campaign.
On a grassy bluff overlooking the ocean, the two models gambol about, photographing each other in a variety of the brand's products.
When you got it: The 25-year-old flung a stylish white coat over a faintly sheer white top that was tight enough to showcase her impressively trim midriff
The Westminster-born actress has not yet commented personally on an alleged hack that Wayne Rooney prostitute Helen Wood discussed in her Daily Star column.
In an article published last week, Wood claimed she'd received a direct message via Twitter containing 'a link to Emily Ratajkowski's iCloud pictures. This clown had inboxed me and asked that I release the full set of naked images in my column.'
She noted: 'To be clear, this wasn't footage of a randy star salivating at the mouth wanging their bits about while fishing for a random on Skype for a sex sesh. This was private stuff, sent between two people.'
Posing up a storm: Her hair wound into an updo, she'd slipped on a pair of high-waisted, loose white slacks and gleaming stilettos
Refusing to release the photos, Wood snapped in her column: 'I know there are some demented people out there, but I cannot get my head around how sick it is.'
MailOnline has heard from a representative from Ratajkowski, who's said the images in question are the same ones hacked and released a view years ago.
The We Are Your Friends star also criticized photographer Jonathan Leder last December for releasing Polaroid images from a racy photo-shoot without her consent. She's tweeted: 'To be clear: I signed no release & was not paid.'
